,Recommended,291960,16159116,"Posted: 3 June, 2015",all,Fluent,"Wow! What a game we have here. If you are a fan of challenging, punishing, brutal games like Dark Souls, and enjoy dungeon-crawling through beautiful dungeons with lots of interesting encounters, gorgeous artwork and enemies to encounter, and much, much more, then you simply have to check this game out.You create a party of 6 adventurers from a variety of classes, races and stats, and head out into the world to explore why monsters have returned from a nearby cave. Well, things start to spiral down from there, and you're dragged into an epic adventure, however, the main draw here is the immersive, first-person dungeon-crawling. The dungeon tiles themselves are decent, but repetitive in their visual appearance. However, the monsters are anything but that. The monster and enemy artwork in this game is ridiculously cool, twisted and surreal. You'll face some really outrageous, creepy and even cringe-inducing enemies, all in high definition on your screen. If there were more variation in the dungeon tiles themselves it would just add to the game, but the monster artwork is more than sufficient.The character development is cool. There are hundreds of unique items to equip and wear, from maces to helmets, as well as other unique loot to find. There are a bunch of classes each with strong advantages and disadvantages that allow you to craft a party of your choosing and discover synergies yourself. You can class switch later on when you meet the stat requirements, and that also has some interesting quirks to it, as you can mix a few traits from different classes that you've already learned. In short, it will keep you playing and developing your party for many hours of old-school CRPG goodness.You will be crawling through all sorts of crazy locations, from maze-like labyrinths, to dungeons with hidden traps around every corner. To find some of the secret locations in the game, you really have to search, and the game does NOT hold your hand for one minute. The game is indeed brutal. The game is modeled after the original Wizardry trilogy, and they do not pull any punches. You'll die, you'll drag your half-dead party back to town only to have the priest turn your characters to ash. Of course, you can re-load your save to fix that, and unfortunately Elminage Gothic does not include a Hardcore or Mania mode that would make saving more of a risk/reward endeavor. Still, the game is tough.If you love challenging games and want to endure the gauntlet in this party-based RPG, just buy the game now. For $9.99 it's an absolute steal since it features over 80+ hours of dungeon-crawling gameplay, with some saying they have played for hundreds of hours due to post-game dungeon content where you will really be tested. And it never gets old because you are never quite sure what's around the next corner, and when you will get brutally murdered next!Try this game now if you're into first-person, dungeon-crawling, old-school RPGs. You will not regret it.10/10!"
