,Recommended,291960,15746526,"Posted: 8 May, 2015",all,Nedragaard,"4/5Seriously... am I playing Wizardry?Elminage is in every way a full on Wizardry clone.  EVERYTHING is the same except the maps.  Even the artwork looks like it was taken from the Wizardy: Proving Grounds booklet from the late 80s.Just because it is a clone game doesn't mean you should pass Elminage by.  If you are into RPGs, you will have a blast with this game.If you'r not familiar with Wizardry, I'll explain.  Wizardy was one of the first RPGs to revolutionize the videogame industry.  Many of the RPGs that were produced for the NES, were inspired by the Wizardy games.  The game starts by forming a party of 6 characters.  You can browse a few places in town such as the Inn and Shop; but most of the game takes place inside an underground maze.  The maze gets harder as you descend, forcing you to make frequent trips to the surface to heal and level up.  The character creation is very in-depth and mimics D&D rules some-what.  Lots of dungoen mapping and slaying :)"
